ğŸ§  Understanding floor('H'):
floor('H') preserves the hour and zeros out only the minute, second, and microsecond.

So:

python
Copy
pd.Timestamp('2024-01-16 14:37:29').floor('H') â†’ 2024-01-16 14:00:00
âœ… This means when we say â€œfloored,â€ we still retain the hour component, just not the minute/second. Thatâ€™s exactly what we want for hourly candle alignment.

So 2024-01-16 14:00:00 is not a mistake â€” it's the 14:00 hourly candle, i.e., from 14:00 to 14:59.

