ChatGPT said:
âœ… Yes â€” the AUC (Area Under the ROC Curve) youâ€™re seeing here:

Measures how well the model ranks positive vs. negative outcomes, regardless of threshold.

ğŸ§  So for your setup:
Positive class = y_test > 0 â†’ the candle closed up from the previous close

Negative class = y_test â‰¤ 0 â†’ candle closed down or flat

ğŸ” AUC is symmetric:
It answers:

If I randomly select one up-close and one down-close, how often does the model score the up-close higher?

AUC = 0.5 â†’ no signal (random guessing)

AUC < 0.5 â†’ reverse signal (model is inverted)

AUC > 0.5 â†’ useful directional discrimination

ğŸš¨ In your results:
SVR has AUC < 0.5 in Q1â€“Q3 â†’ itâ€™s worse than random (could be inverted)

